				<td colspan="2"><span>Greetings and salutations all.
<br />

<br />
I apologize if you've heard this question a million times, but I just started up a bard, and well... I'm having some problems.
<br />

<br />
Having a level 65 cleric as my main, it took a bit of adjusting.  First I tried charm kiting.. but charm kept breaking every few seconds.  Then I switched to AE kiting, and had very good success up until level 28.  Even now I have no problem kiting down 12-15 yellow mobs at a time.  However, the problem is once I get the mobs almost dead, they simply vanish... they don't run.. just poof, gone.
<br />

<br />
I've heard that this is some kind of terrain bug.  It didn't happen to me often when I while I was leveling in LOIO, but it did happen on occassion.  I tried kiting in EW and 95% of the mobs disapear in a fashion similar to what I described above.  
<br />

<br />
Is this a new bug?  What zones are safe from its effect?  Or am I doing something seriously wrong?  Thank you very much for your time.
<br />

<br />

<br />
-Masaedis Goblinblight- 65 cleric 
<br />
-Stryxion- 29 bard
<br />
-Druzzil Ro.</span></td>
