				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Vanishing Mobs.<a name="19564"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 6 04 12:02 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I usually chant kite things down as I travel around.  I enjoy the control of it more then swarm kiting.  What I do is chant them down untill they are at about 25-20% using all four chants and a sow potion then I drop one chant and add the snare.  Once they turn to run and they are locked in place with the snare I will drop one of the chants so I am only twisting three songs (Two DOTs and one Snare).  This insures that I can keep the mob locked down.  A little lag or a missed note can be recovered.
<br />

<br />
I have had mobs that were snared but because I was trying to keep 4 soungs going and the snare breaks because the twist goes a little screwy the mob has poof instantly.
<br />

<br />
Give it a try I know it sounds like you are adding more time to the fight but you will be safer and you wont lose the exp!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
