				<td colspan="2"><span>I have tested this and found that in groups if we sing our snare song, we have a chance of mobs poofing.  PoN I was grouped and 3-10 poofed when I sang my AoE snare slow song.  I stopped singing song and druid snared and for 2 hours not a single one poofed.  I then went to ME to try solo and again Poof.  
<br />

<br />
The only way that I have found to get them not to poof, is to maintain 2-5 in the swarm at all times.  As soon as my mana gets low I usually dont bother with the last couple as I know that it will poof and let the zone know that Im headed to the zone with a train.
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps out, I've pretty much given up on solo, since grouping is more fun, and yields more xp/plat at my current season of 55</span></td>
